    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-08T04:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-08T04:35:00-05:00" n="366"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1869: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-08T13:00:00+03:25"
                            >May 8, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 8—12:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>145. Department’s 116, May 5 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>].<note n="72"
                        xml:id="d366fn72">Not printed; it informed the Minister in Iran concerning
                        Department’s instructions to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union contained in
                        telegram No. 203, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Prime Minister
                    informed me last night he had received a satisfactory reply from his appeal to
                    Molotov reported in my 138, May 3. The reply states that Soviet military
                    authorities have been instructed to collaborate with Iranian authorities with a
                    view to sending Iranian troops to disturbed areas.</p>
                <p>Minister of War<note n="73" xml:id="d366fn73">Gen. Amanollah Jahanbani.</note>
                    and several other officials have already arrived in Azerbaijan to arrange the
                    details with Soviet authorities.</p>
                <p>A despatch on entire situation is being airmailed.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Kuibyshev.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
